Under  Section  136 
(1) 
(b)  of  the  Code  of  Criminal  Procedure  Act
(hereinafter  referred  to  as  the  "Code")  institution  of proceedings  in  a

Magistrate's  Court  (in  addition  to  certain  other  modes) 
takes  place

upon 
the 
presentation 
of 
a  written 
report 
complaining  of 
the
commission  of an  offence.  The  proceedings  in  this  case  had  begun

with 
the  complainant-respondent-respondent  filing  a 
report  under

Section  136 
(1) 
(b)  of  the  Code  complaining  that  the  accused  had
